results.summary: Construction of Sarajevo Prison
results.content: Construction of Sarajevo Prison

description: In an effort to strengthen the rule of law in Bosnia and Herzegovina and enhance the integrity of judiciary and law enforcement, the European Union to BiH assists in improving the capacities for the execution of criminal sanctions. Through IPA 2017 and 2019, funds are provided to advance the suitability of the Detention Unit of the Sarajevo Correctional Facility by building a new complex. This action shall allow the relocation from the current building in the city centre, to a new location. The preparation of the preliminary design for the new prison complex was supported by EU and the preparation of the Main Design was funded by Federal Ministry of Justice. The construction and the supervision of the works will be funded by the EU. The new complex will comprise 4 buildings, namely entrance control, accommodation, administration, and service facility and will accommodate 150 male inmates in a total gross building area of 4 375 m2.
title: Construction of Sarajevo Prison

results.summary: Works for Adaptation and Reconstruction of the Cross Border Railway Station Building, Bijelo Polje
results.content: Works for Adaptation and Reconstruction of the Cross Border Railway Station Building, Bijelo Polje

description: The purpose of the project is the improvement of transport conditions and travel times on the railway corridor Bar–Vrbnica. In this context the tenderer will provide construction works for the adaptation and reconstruction of the existing cross border railway station building Bijelo Polje on the Bar - Vrbnica railway line to become a joint border station between Montenegro and Serbia, in accordance with the Montenegrin legislation and EU standards. The construction works will provide appropriate working conditions and enable parallel control for Montenegrin and Serbian cross border authorities. This will exclude the need for double stopping of trains and decrease custom control/travel time by 30 min.The works contract will be implemented under the General Conditions for Works Contracts financed by the European Union Budget or the European Development Fund (EDF).
title: Works for Adaptation and Reconstruction of the Cross Border Railway Station Building, Bijelo Polje

results.summary: Support to EU SMEs on EU sanctions due diligence
results.content: Support to EU SMEs on EU sanctions due diligence

description: The action is intended to support European operators, especially Small and Medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), having to abide by EU sanctions. It will set up an EU Sanctions Due Diligence Helpdesk and develop operational tools necessary for its functioning. The Helpdesk would act as central contact point for EU SMEs having questions concerning due diligence for specific business projects in countries subject to EU sanctions. The Helpdesk will reassure operators who need to comply with the applicable European restrictions, and may put the focus on sensitive areas of high political or economic importance, such as agri-food trade and humanitarian assistance. The Helpdesk would also organise trainings to raise awareness on EU sanctions. The action will also help reassure European banks, which may be currently reluctant to handle transactions involving countries subject to sanctions.
title: Support to EU SMEs on EU sanctions due diligence

description: The activity will aim to improve social protection system performance to create a supportive environment for quality community-based social services, non-institutional support, and active inclusion of vulnerable groups in the labour market. The above is pre-requisite preparation for ESF measures of promoting active inclusion and active participation, developing evidence-based diagnosis and policies supporting the shift from institutional to community-based care while also being gender responsive. Interventions will initially be based on institutional and capacity building support to the Ministry in charge of social policy and the Republic and Province Institute for Social protection. The social protection system will be modernised to enhance non-institutional care and timely access to quality and sustainable, community-based social services for the most disadvantaged women and men, boys and girls.
title: Improving and strengthening efficiency of national social protection regulatory mechanisms, policy implementation tools, quality assurance framework and strengthening capacities to participate in ESF

description: The contracting authority envisages the implementation of a vocational training programme addressing relevant economic sectors in the Litani River Basin (LRB). This programme, targeting mainly youth, will be linked to the needs of the local markets, and to businesses and industries in LRB to secure internship and jobs opportunities for successful candidates. The foreseen training programme will consist of a combination of occupational and soft skills. The occupational skills will include fields such as, industrial mechanics, industrial electricians, Lebanese gastronomy, international gastronomy, local food marketing, and software development. Soft skills will touch skills such as information technology, English language, communication skills and others. The training programme will be certified by international training agencies. Environmental compliance will be a crosscutting element of learning and practice in the vocational training.
